analysis:
Sentiment analysis from last week (2025-08-01 to 2025-08-07) to this week (2025-08-10 to 2025-08-12):

**Positive Developments:**
* JPMoorgan Chase is presenting at the Barclays Global Financial Services Conference (2025-08-12).
* Big Tech is driving the stock market to new records (2025-08-12).
* Goldman Sachs' strong liquidity may aid its capital distribution strategy (2025-08-12).
* J.P. Morgan Self-Directed Investing was named Best Online Brokerage (2025-08-12).
* JPMoorgan Chase is in advanced talks to take over Apple's credit card program (2025-08-11).
* JPMoorgan's Peters forecasts equities 7%-8% higher over the next 12 months (2025-08-11).
* JPMoorgan brings forward Fed rate cut forecast to September (2025-08-05).
* JPMoorgan, Bank of America shares slide as Trump says banks discriminated against him (2025-08-05).
* JPMoorgan's David Kelly suggests a healthy economy (2025-08-04).
* If $1,000 was invested in JPMoorgan Chase 5 years ago, the return would be significant (2025-08-04).

**Negative Factors/Risks:**
* Trump says major US banks 'discriminated against me' as White House prepares a debanking executive order (2025-08-05).
* The worst of the tariffs may still be to come (2025-08-04).
* Decentralized Finance and Tokenization growth is disappointing (2025-08-07).
* JPM downgrades International Paper, indicating investor hopes for 2027 look too high (2025-08-05).
* Sllowing labor demand will lead the Fed to deliver rate cuts later this year (2025-08-04).
* Corporate America remains focused on stock buybacks (2025-08-05).

**Sentiment Outlook for Today (2025-08-12):**
The sentiment for today is neutral, as indicated by the lack of specific sentiment values for the day.
